data.chText: 不可避免的；不能防止的
data.enText: that you cannot avoid or prevent

data.chText: 那是这个决定的必然后果。
data.enText: It was an inevitable consequence of the decision.

data.chText: 裁员已是不可避免的事。
data.enText: It was inevitable that there would be job losses.

data.chText: 提高利率似乎是不可避免的。
data.enText: A rise in the interest rates seems inevitable.

data.chText: 总会发生的；照例必有的；惯常的
data.enText: so frequent that you always expect it

data.chText: 英格兰人和他们例行的饮茶
data.enText: the English and their inevitable cups of tea

data.chText: 必然发生的事；不可避免的事
data.enText: something that is certain to happen

data.chText: 你得接受必然发生的事。
data.enText: You have to accept the inevitable.

data.chText: 逃不掉的事情发生了——我忘了带护照。
data.enText: The inevitable happened─I forgot my passport.

data.chText: 他们的失败自有其必然。
data.enText: There was an inevitability about their defeat.

word_means: 必然发生的事；不可避免的事
simple_means.memory_skill: in 不，无，非 + evitable 可避免的 → 不可避免的

means: 必然发生的事；不可避免的事

tr: incapable of being avoided or prevented

example: the inevitable changes of the seasons

value.def: If something is inevitable, it is certain to happen and cannot be prevented or avoided.

example.ex: If the case succeeds, it is inevitable that other trials will follow...
example.tran: 如果该案胜诉,其他审判必然随之而来。

example.ex: The defeat had inevitable consequences for British policy.
example.tran: 战败对英国政策不可避免地产生了影响。

posc.def: The inevitable is something which is inevitable.

example.ex: 'It's just delaying the inevitable,' he said.
example.tran: “那仅仅会延迟不可避免之事的发生,”他说。

value.tran: 不可避免的;无法规避的;必然(发生)的
